    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and sprinkle over your <strong>dried basil </strong>and <strong>dried oregano </strong>and drizzle over a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give the chicken a good mix up until coated in the herbs</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong>, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is cooking, add your <strong>pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic is fragrant, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ground paprika</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until wilted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, slice the<strong> cooked chicken </strong>on a clean chopping board</p><p>Cut your <strong>sun-dried tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>pasta</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), <strong>sliced chicken </strong>and the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>sun-dried tomatoes</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato chicken pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-sun-dried-tomato-chicken-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato chicken pasta</strong> and sprinkle with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
